<b>Amit Singhal</b> is a <company wordnetid="108058098" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../923/1092923.xml">
Google</link></company>
 Fellow. According to the <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../680/30680.xml">
New York Times</link>, <it>Mr. Singhal is the master of what Google calls its “ranking algorithm” — the formulas that decide which Web pages best answer each user’s question</it>. A native of <country wordnetid="108544813" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../533/14533.xml">
India</link></country>
, Amit got his bachelors degree in Computer Science from <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../412/315412.xml">
IIT Roorkee</link> in 1989. Amit holds an MS in Computer Science from <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../285/563285.xml">
University of Minnesota Duluth</link></university>
, and a Ph.D. in Computer Science from <university wordnetid="108286163" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../422/7954422.xml">
Cornell University</link></university>
 in Ithaca, NY. At Cornell Amit studied with <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
<peer wordnetid="109626238" confidence="0.8">
<person wordnetid="100007846" confidence="0.8">
<pioneer wordnetid="110434725" confidence="0.8">
<colleague wordnetid="109935990" confidence="0.8">
<causal_agent wordnetid="100007347" confidence="0.8">
