</person>
</peer>
</physical_entity>
, a pioneer in the field of Information Retrieval, the academic discipline which forms the foundation of modern search. John Battelle, in his book "The Search" call Gerrard Salton "the father of digital search."<p>

Amit got interested in the problem of search in 1990 at University of Minnesota. After getting a Ph.D. in search in 1996, Amit joined AT&amp;T Labs (previously a part of Bell Labs), and continued his research in search and other related fields. In 2000, he was persuaded by his friend <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../954/2623954.xml">
Krishna Bharat</link> to join Google. Amit runs a team in Google's Search Quality group. He is and his team are responsible for the Google search algorithms.</p>

